roject was completed in 2013 after four years of construction. <br>De Rotterdam is part of the ongoing redevelopment of the city’s old harbour district of Wilhelminapier</span> <span class=\"element-image__credit\">Photograph: Matteo Rossi/Artur Images</span> </figcaption> </figure>  <figure class=\"element element-image\" data-media-id=\"b57f09d4f42c29240e50f6e687927ec7fa8f1c86\"> <img src=\"https://media.guim.co.uk/b57f09d4f42c29240e50f6e687927ec7fa8f1c86/0_0_4141_5277/785.jpg\" alt=\"Trans World Airlines (TWA) Terminal, JFK Airport, New York, New York, USA, 1962 by Eero Saarinen and Associates\" width=\"785\" height=\"1000\" class=\"gu-image\" /> <figcaption> <span class=\"element-image__caption\"><strong>TWA Terminal, New York</strong><br><br>Eero Saarinen was commissioned to design a terminal at JFK airport that would ‘capture the spirit of flight’. Construction started in 1956 and was completed in 1962, a year after Saarinen died of a brain tumour. Named a New York City landmark in 1994, it has been unused since 2001 as it couldn’t handle larger aircraft. Last year it was announced the building would be redeveloped as a hotel</span> <span class=\"element-image__credit\">Photograph: Library of Congress</span> </figcaption> </figure>  <figure class=\"element element-image\" data-media-id=\"83cb79bb876138e8f86ab5d50bbaaff80034eaaf\"> <img src=\"https://media.guim.co.uk/83cb79bb876138e8f86ab5d50bbaaff80034eaaf/0_0_4173_3406/1000.jpg\" alt=\"Sunset Chapel, Acapulco, Mexico, 2011 by Bunker Arquitectura\" width=\"1000\" height=\"816\" class=\"gu-image\" /> <figcaption> <span class=\"element-image__caption\"><strong>Sunset Chapel, Acapulco</strong><br><strong><br></strong>A building to celebrate life and mourn death, in 2011 Mexican architects Bunker Arquitectura designed this chapel on the idea of contrasts: glass vs concrete, classical proportions vs apparent chaos. <br>Situated on Acapulco’s hills which are made of large granite rocks, it was designed to look like 